“The damage has already been done” is probably the most frequent comment I’ve seen regarding these military cases. 

And while yes, it’s tragic that some service members were either forced out or caved and got the 💉 - let me explain.

Litigating against the government on behalf of active-duty service members is nearly impossible. 

Unlike citizens or federal employees, service members can’t just walk into court and file a lawsuit; they must exhaust all intra-military remedies first.

The other 33 lawyers and I worked tirelessly on our own respective cases. We had to dismantle immunity arguments, ripeness arguments, and a slew of other hurdles the government threw at us. But we never stopped.

While Congress may have passed a bill calling for the mandate’s rescission, make no mistake:

Congress did it to save face, horse traded in doing so, and if it wasn’t for these 33 attorneys I’m proud to say I worked with, nothing would’ve been done.

If you’re going to thank anyone, go back to the first slide–there’s a list of 33 people who deserve it.

Love can’t be defined.

Many, if it not all of us have likely believed we’ve experienced it, but the moment you truly do, it’s the most unequivocally clear sentiment you’ll ever experience.

Love is often conflated.

The vast difference between “loving” someone and being “in love” with “the one” is greater than the human mind can comprehend. Both are needed; the distinction, however, rests in the latter as it applies to one, single person out of 7.8 billion.

Love is not always glamorous.

Life is grand when times are docile. Relishing in moments of elation & during times of celebration is indeed joyous—so joyous in fact, a stranger’s company is readily accepted a welcomed addition. But that is not love.

Love is necessary and must never become acquainted with compromise.

To succeed in life and fulfill the reason God blessed us with life on earth, we must consistently grow not only in faith, but as people. To do so requires great strength, so much so that at a point in life, each of us will become incapable of further developing alone.

You need your partner, and God assuredly created yours. 

To those who celebrate life today alongside their intended other half, I’m sure the aforesaid hits home. 

And to those who have yet to find yours, or those who may think you’ve found the one—but do not know with certainty that you have—do not quit. Do not settle. Do not compromise. 

I promise you: Upon discovering your person, never again will a day on earth bear mimic the days you've lived without him or her in your life. The amelioration your person will bring to your life will render you unrecognizable in the most positive of ways.

Indeed, there is no feeling greater that exists than that of being in true love.
